<br>
Picture a wizard at about 60 percent health but about 90m and too dang impatient to wait any longer before taking on a, um... I think 35ish troll shaman and pet (npc). Anyway said wizard fries shaman in about 30 seconds. Hahaha. Gloats. Shaman did land a spell, one of those diseasy things, and other than that didn't even touch him weee! <br>
<br>
Wizard then has the pet to deal with, had him rooted out of the way till now. Pet comes at him, wizard gets bit a few times, not too hard though, maybe 30s to 50s, couple of them, probly not even 100 damage total.  He is casually leading the pet around, shooting him with lightning and stuff, about one shot to go to kill it and then he realizes HOLY CRAP! under a bubble health left! And that scourge whatever thing aint even blinkin yet!!. No time to waste killing the pet, the wizard needs to bandage RIGHT NOW to live. (Scourge takes about 24 per tick and bandaging heals 25 per bandage. Anyone who has ever bandaged knows one tick is much much faster. Heheh you see where this is going)<br>
<br>
The wizard gates (bind point = Firiona Bank). Scrambles with bandages, flinging them all around while desperately trying to apply first aid to the festering icky crud creeping all over him. The bank is a mess, Wella is screamin at him to clean the place up, Wellford is grabbin a club, scourge is blinking, probably one or two blinks to go and... the wizard drops over dead. Wellford puts the club down.  <br>
<br>
Cheesy way to go. I am not sure if it is more worthless than diving headlong off the cliff in Warsilks 'cause you are running and talking on the winds, but it has to be darn close. Killing something then dying 2 minutes later because of a spell it cast on you and no way you can stop it... Ugh.<br>
<br>
On the bright side, finding my corpse was easy. I just looked down at my feet and there it was. <br>
<br>
Thanks again for making a potential bad night turn into a good night, i.e. I got to meet you and Eldratu <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Hmm... I think I will die more often...<br>
<br>
Caladril<br>
